  "text": "Sections (5 μm thick) were stained with hematoxylin-eosin to measure migratory tongue length. For this, slides were digitalized using Pannoramic Digital Slide Scanner (3DHistech Ltd., Budapest, Hungary). The migratory tongue length was measured using Pannoramic Viewer software (3DHistech Ltd., Budapest, Hungary). Length was defined as the distance (in micrometers) from the wound edge to the tip of the tongue as described [CITATION_1] . The results were presented in μm.",
